sentences.english: As it Dongmei sang songs of early spring.
sentences.chinese: 就象那冬梅吟唱着早春的歌聲。

sentences.english: I expect food inflation to subside by early spring.
sentences.chinese: 我預測，今年早春時節，食品通脹就能消退。

sentences.english: Cutting late autumn or early spring, also decked film to prevent harm winter.
sentences.chinese: 早春或晚秋扦插時，還應加蓋薄膜，以防冬害。

sentences.english: The kapok is in blossom that heralds the early spring.
sentences.chinese: 木棉花的綻放預報着早春的到來。

sentences.english: The flower comes out in early spring.
Apple trees bear blossoms in early spring.
The early spring wind smooth as water.
Herds are fattening on the early clover.
sentences.chinese: 家畜喫早春的苜蓿而上膘。

sentences.english: It was too early in the spring for Sukey to be let out in the Big Woods to eat grass.
sentences.chinese: 早春時節，把蘇姬放到森林裏喫草還嫌太早。

sentences.english: In early spring the plants usually starts to flower.
sentences.chinese: 捕蟲樹一般在早春開花。

sentences.english: Good weather in early spring allowed them to forage for nectar.
sentences.chinese: 在早春溫暖氣候下，它們就可以採集花蜜了。

sentences.english: I worm all my birds in early spring.
sentences.chinese: 早春的時候我給我所有的鳥打蟲。

sentences.english: Starch grains decreased progressively after cambial activity was resumed in early spring until they disappeared in all the stem tissues.
sentences.chinese: 早春形成層恢復活動後，澱粉貯量逐漸減少直至消失。

sentences.english: It is my great pleasure to visit Germany again in the early spring, a time of the revivification of nature.
sentences.chinese: 我很高興在萬物復甦的早春時節再次來到德國。

sentences.english: The reproduction of T. viennensis in early spring had significant difference with that in the summer population.
sentences.chinese: 山楂葉蟎早春的生殖力與夏季種羣差異顯著。

definition: early autumn/7th month of the lunar calendar
Chunri or Chunjih township in Pingtung County 屏東縣|屏东县[Ping2 dong1 Xian4], Taiwan
(of plants) to turn green again/to revegetate
